summary: This is an FBI FD-302 form documenting the execution of a search warrant at 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, on July 11, 2019. The warrant, signed by Judge Henry Pittman, authorized a search for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy. The document details the execution process, participants, and documentation created.

events.title: Search Warrant Execution at 9 East 71st Street
events.description: FBI agents and NYPD officers executed a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's New York residence at 9 East 71st Street. The warrant authorized a search for evidence, fruits, and instrumentalities of violations of sex trafficking of minors and sex trafficking conspiracy, including computer devices and storage media.

United States District Court for the Southern District of New York
keyFacts: A search warrant was executed at Jeffrey Epstein's New York residence (9 East 71st Street) on July 11, 2019, at 2:35 pm.

The warrant was issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York and signed by Judge Henry Pittman, authorizing a search for evidence of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.
The search was conducted by a team of FBI agents and NYPD officers, and agents documented the scene with logs, diagrams, and photographs.
The document is an official FBI FD-302 form, indicating it is a factual report of the investigation and not containing recommendations or conclusions.
